"[{\"question\": \"What is PureWay OC?\", \"answer\": \"PureWay OC is a professional service provider serving Orange County, CA. Medical-grade whole-house water filtration for Orange County homes. Free water test, same-day response, lifetime warranty. Powered by Toppen Health.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Where is PureWay OC located?\", \"answer\": \"PureWay OC is located at  and serves Orange County, CA.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I contact PureWay OC?\", \"answer\": \"Call (949) 998-9443, visit https://purewayoc.com, or use the online contact form at https://purewayoc.com/contact.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com/contact\"}, {\"question\": \"How long has PureWay OC been in business?\", \"answer\": \"PureWay OC is an established local provider with a proven track record in Orange County.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com/about\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the difference between a water softener and a water filter?\", \"answer\": \"A water softener removes hardness minerals \\u2014 calcium and magnesium \\u2014 through ion exchange to prevent scale buildup. A water filter removes contaminants such as chlorine, sediment, heavy metals, and PFAS to improve taste, odor, and safety. Many homeowners benefit from both systems working together.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I know if I need a water softener?\", \"answer\": \"Signs of hard water include white scale deposits on faucets and showerheads, soap that lathers poorly, dingy laundry, and shortened appliance lifespan. A free water test measures hardness in grains per gallon (GPG); water above 7 GPG is typically considered hard and benefits from softening.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How long does a water softener last?\", \"answer\": \"A quality water softener typically lasts 15-25 years with proper maintenance. Annual salt replenishment, periodic resin bed cleaning, and a pre-filter to reduce sediment loading are the primary maintenance tasks that protect system longevity.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Is softened water safe to drink?\", \"answer\": \"Yes, softened water is safe to drink for most people. The ion exchange process adds a small amount of sodium \\u2014 roughly 20-40 mg per 8 oz glass, depending on original hardness. Individuals on sodium-restricted diets may prefer a dedicated reverse osmosis tap for drinking water.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I get started?\", \"answer\": \"Getting started is simple: call or submit the online contact form to schedule a free consultation. During the consultation, goals and expectations are discussed, a site assessment is completed if needed, and a written proposal is delivered within 48 hours.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How much does a water softener cost to install?\", \"answer\": \"Water softener installation typically ranges from $800 to $2,500 depending on system capacity (measured in grains), brand, and local labor rates. High-efficiency salt-free systems or whole-home filtration bundles range from $2,000 to $5,000 installed. Most systems pay for themselves within 3-5 years through reduced appliance repairs and lower soap/detergent costs.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How much does a reverse osmosis system cost?\", \"answer\": \"Under-sink reverse osmosis systems cost $300-$700 installed. Whole-home RO systems for well water range from $1,500 to $4,000. Annual filter replacement costs $50-$150 per year for under-sink units.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Do you offer free estimates?\", \"answer\": \"Yes, free estimates are provided for all projects. Estimates include a detailed scope of work, itemized pricing, and a realistic timeline so there are no surprises.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Why is professional water treatment important?\", \"answer\": \"85% of U.S. homes have hard water (U.S. Geological Survey, 2024). Water softeners can extend appliance lifespan by up to 30% (Water Quality Association, 2023). Hard water causes $800-$1,000 in annual energy waste per household (Department of Energy, 2023). These figures underscore why professional service from a company like PureWay OC represents a sound investment.\", \"category\": \"education\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Does PureWay OC serve Irvine, CA?\", \"answer\": \"Yes. PureWay OC provides medical-grade whole-house water filtration, water softeners, reverse osmosis, and free water testing in Irvine, CA. Irvine is one of PureWay OC's primary service cities. Call (949) 998-9443 to schedule your free water test in Irvine.\", \"category\": \"local\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com/service-area\"}, {\"question\": \"Does PureWay OC serve Anaheim, CA?\", \"answer\": \"Yes. PureWay OC serves Anaheim and all of Orange County with medical-grade water filtration powered by Toppen Health Disruptor PAC technology. Call (949) 998-9443 to schedule your free water test in Anaheim.\", \"category\": \"local\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com/service-area\"}, {\"question\": \"Does PureWay OC serve Huntington Beach, CA?\", \"answer\": \"Yes. PureWay OC serves Huntington Beach with whole-house water filtration, reverse osmosis, and water softeners. Same-day response and free water testing available. Call (949) 998-9443.\", \"category\": \"local\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com/service-area\"}, {\"question\": \"What is Toppen Health Disruptor PAC technology?\", \"answer\": \"Toppen Health Disruptor PAC is the medical-grade filtration technology powering PureWay OC systems. PAC (Powered Activated Carbon) technology delivers 99.99% contaminant removal \\u2014 a level of purification typically found only in medical and laboratory settings. PureWay OC is one of the few residential water treatment companies in Orange County offering this level of filtration.\", \"category\": \"education\", \"url\": \"https://purewayoc.com\"}]"